   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Forty-two GRACE, REDEMPTION, AND JUSTIFICATION Scripture: Rom 3:24 Grace Grace is the expression and manifestation of God s love.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Grace is something freely given of God or done by God.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>God freely saves and justifies us; He did something for us and gave us something freely.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Redemption Redemption is necessitated by God s righteousness.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>God s righteousness requires that He accomplish redemption for us.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>God s redemption is accomplished by the crucifixion of Jesus Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The death of Christ on the cross satisfies the requirement of God s righteousness so that God s grace can come to us freely.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Justification Justification is the grace of God to save us according to the righteousness of God.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Therefore, justification is both grace bestowed upon us and God s righteousness accomplished for us.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>It is God s love that causes Him to have grace upon us, and God s righteousness which causes Him to accomplish redemption for us.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Therefore, because of justification, God can reckon us righteous and is able to save us.</S>
   </TEXT>
